claim.claim-text:
11. An articulation joint for a medical device, comprising:
a plurality of connectors, each connector including:
a body portion defining a first lumen and having a planar end that is substantially planar in a transverse direction to a longitudinal axis of the body portion;
an insert portion extending axially and radially away from the planar end of the body portion and defining a second lumen extending from the first lumen of the body portion;
a slot extending through a middle and sides of the insertion portion; and
a plurality of openings axially extending through a wall of the body portion and positioned around the first lumen;
wherein the insert portion of a connector is configured to be inserted into a first lumen of an adjacent connector to couple the connector to the adjacent connector.

15. An articulation joint of claim 11, wherein the body portion completely surrounds the first lumen;
wherein the first lumen opens into the second lumen, the first lumen includes a diameter larger than a diameter of the second lumen, a cross-sectional shape of the first lumen is complementary with a cross-sectional shape of the insert portion, and the insert portion includes a diameter smaller than a diameter of the body portion;
wherein each opening extends axially through the body portion from a first end of the body portion to a second end of the body portion;
wherein, when the insert portion is inserted into the first lumen of the adjacent connector, the body portion surrounds the outer surface of the insert portion; and
wherein the first lumens of adjacent connectors are in flow communication with each other.
